When your Pioneer mini split system has the smart WiFi module installed, and you have configured the Pioneer AirLink app, you can tie in Alexa integration and ask Alexa to do various things with your Pioneer mini split, such as turn it on/off, change modes and temperatures, and monitor the health of the system. You can also program regular custom schedules for what you'd like the AC to do at certain days and times. The only limit is your imagination.

You can simply ask Alexa to control your devices. After connecting Alexa to your products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our “Pioneer Airlink” app in app market then register an account;
(2). Configure our devices in our “Pioneer Airlink” app and change appropriate name for your devices;
(3). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market then configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(4). Search “Pioneer Smart AC Link” skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(5). Enable “Pioneer Smart AC Link” skill, and you'll be navigated to “Pioneer Smart AC Link” login page;
(6). Follow the instructions on the page to complete linking;
(7). Now all setup is finished. You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on AC.”
“Alexa, turn off AC”
